<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-8a-1-1">
	<statement>
		<p>
			Let <m>f(x)=e^x</m> and <m>Q(x) = c_0 + c_1 x + c_2 x^2</m>.  We seek numerical values for the constants <m>c_0</m>, <m>c_1</m>, and <m>c_2</m> so that <m>f(0)=Q(0)</m>, <m>f'(0)=Q'(0)</m>, and <m>f''(0)=Q''(0)</m>.
		</p>
		<p>
			<ol marker="a.">
				<li>
				<p>
					Note that since <m>c_0</m>, <m>c_1</m>, and <m>c_2</m> are constants, if we take the derivative of the quadratic function <m>Q</m> using <xref ref="sum-rule" text="title"></xref> and <xref ref="const-mult-rule" text="title"></xref>, it follows that <m>Q’(x) = c_1 + 2 c_2 x</m>.  
				</p>

				<p>
					What is <m>Q’’(x)</m>?
				</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Recall that <m>f(x) = e^x</m>.  Determine <m>f’(x)</m> and <m>f’’(x)</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Enter the formulas you've determined for <m>f(x)</m>, <m>f'(x)</m>, <m>f''(x)</m>, <m>Q(x)</m>, <m>Q'(x)</m>, and <m>Q''(x)</m> in the first three rows of <xref ref="T-act-8a-1-1">Table</xref>.

						<table xml:id="T-act-8a-1-1">
						<title>Formulas and values for <m>f(x)</m> and <m>Q(x)</m>.</title>
							<tabular top="minor" bottom="minor">
								<row>
									<cell><m>f(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
									<cell><m>Q(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell><m>f'(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
									<cell><m>Q'(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>                
								<row>
									<cell><m>f''(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
									<cell><m>Q''(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell></cell>
									<cell></cell>
									<cell></cell>
									<cell></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell><m>f(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
									<cell><m>Q(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell><m>f'(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
									<cell><m>Q'(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>                
								<row>
									<cell><m>f''(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
									<cell><m>Q''(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
							</tabular>
						</table>
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Next, observe that since <m>Q(x) = c_0 + c_1 x + c_2 x^2</m>, it follows that <m>Q(0) = c_0</m>.  Reason similarly to determine the values of <m>Q'(0)</m> and <m>Q''(0)</m>, as well as those of <m>f(0)</m>, <m>f'(0)</m>, and <m>f''(0)</m> and enter these 6 values appropriately in the last three rows of <xref ref="T-act-8a-1-1">Table</xref>.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Now, recall that we want the function values, first derivative values, and second derivative values of <m>f</m> and <m>Q</m> to match at <m>a = 0</m>.  What does <m>Q(0) = f(0)</m> tell us about the value of <m>c_0</m>? What does <m>Q’(0) = f’(0)</m> tell us about the value of <m>c_1</m>? What does <m>Q’’(0) = f’’(0)</m> tell you about the value of <m>c_2</m>?  
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Having now determined the numerical values of <m>c_0</m>, <m>c_1</m>, and <m>c_2</m>, plot the function <m>Q(x) = c_0 + c_1 x + c_2 x^2</m> along with <m>f(x)=e^x</m> and <m>L(x)=1+x</m> in <xref ref="F-8a-1-act-1">Figure</xref>.  What do you notice?  For about which values of <m>x</m> is <m>|f(x)-Q(x)| \lt 0.1</m>?

